summary:
I am a Strategy Consultant at the Australian Institute of Sport (AIS). I specialise in creating value for organisations and stakeholders in highly competitive environments. Through my work with Olympians, Paralympians, and their supporting organisations, I have seen firsthand how even the slightest edge over competitors can create significant advantages in output.
I have skills in advising organisations on a range of economic and commercial issues with key skills in team and project management, strategy design and execution, stakeholder engagement, gap analysis, organisation capability, operations modelling, data analysis, workshop facilitation, and accounting, financial and legal analysis.
